cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CR, cs.NE 

The paper discusses a Python package for generating adversarial perturbations and benchmarking the robustness of machine learning models. This topic is closely related to several sub-categories of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), cryptography and security (cs.CR), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). Among these, cs.LG and cs.CV are the most likely categories as they are directly related to the topic of machine learning model robustness and adversarial attacks.
